1
00:00:42,640 --> 00:00:44,759
Did you see Xiao Lian?

2
00:00:50,240 --> 00:00:51,719
Don't worry, Auntie Ling.

3
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:53,240
I saw my sister's troops.

4
00:00:53,240 --> 00:00:53,759
I bolted right out of there.

5
00:00:53,759 --> 00:00:55,280
Speak up!

6
00:00:56,119 --> 00:00:56,719
Auntie Ling.

7
00:00:57,280 --> 00:00:58,159
Look at him.

8
00:00:58,439 --> 00:00:59,520
He gets worked up over Xiao Lian.

9
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:00,719
This old man.

10
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:01,719
He plays favorites.

11
00:01:02,799 --> 00:01:03,679
I'm asking you a question.

12
00:01:03,679 --> 00:01:04,920
How is Xiao Lian, really?

13
00:01:05,719 --> 00:01:06,400
Reporting, Master.

14
00:01:07,079 --> 00:01:07,879
Xiao Lian's doing just fine.

15
00:01:08,439 --> 00:01:09,560
She outranks me now.

16
00:01:10,640 --> 00:01:11,760
Well, I'll be damned.

17
00:01:13,959 --> 00:01:14,400
Fine then.

18
00:01:15,159 --> 00:01:16,120
Once you're done...

19
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:17,040
...let's get going.

20
00:01:17,920 --> 00:01:19,480
What's the rush?

21
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:20,920
Auntie Ling.

22
00:01:21,599 --> 00:01:22,719
Just go with that stubborn old man.

23
00:01:23,719 --> 00:01:24,519
Master's getting old.

24
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:27,400
You...

25
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:28,680
Drop by home when you can.

26
00:01:28,959 --> 00:01:30,319
Your master bought these for you.

27
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:33,439
Thanks for the tomatoes, Master.

28
00:01:42,359 --> 00:01:43,079
Who's there?

29
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:44,760
Military secret.

30
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:45,519
No comment.

31
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:50,120
Have a swig.

32
00:02:06,959 --> 00:02:08,439
Why isn't this water hot?

33
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:11,680
We can't afford firewood anymore.

34
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:12,719
Old man.

35
00:02:13,560 --> 00:02:15,120
If you don't bring some money home soon,

36
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:17,000
forget about water for your feet,

37
00:02:17,439 --> 00:02:19,560
we won't even have food on the table.

38
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:22,199
The weather's been nice these days.

39
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:24,280
No one needs their shoes shined.

40
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:28,879
Old man.

41
00:02:29,879 --> 00:02:31,479
Someone just walked by.

42
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:35,120
I'll go check.

43
00:02:35,319 --> 00:02:36,719
I'll dump the foot water while I'm at it.

44
00:02:51,599 --> 00:02:52,280
Who's there?

45
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:02,240
Old man!

46
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:03,840
What is it?

47
00:03:04,159 --> 00:03:05,000
Old man!

48
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:06,680
Old man!

49
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:09,599
Old man!

50
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:30,680
Roads are slick in the rain.

51
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,800
Watch for puddles.

52
00:03:35,319 --> 00:03:37,000
Roads are slick in the rain.

53
00:03:37,199 --> 00:03:39,000
Watch for puddles.

54
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:43,439
I can't wait any longer.

55
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:45,520
We're almost at my place.

56
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:48,240
Right here is fine.

57
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:51,400
It's the dead of night, no one's around.

58
00:03:51,520 --> 00:03:54,000
Sky as our blanket, ground as our bed.

59
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:56,319
Let's be wild lovebirds, you and me.

60
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:04,319
A ghost!

61
00:04:06,879 --> 00:04:08,439
Ghost!

62
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:14,639
Lao Jiugui.

63
00:04:15,039 --> 00:04:16,279
How did she actually die?

64
00:04:17,079 --> 00:04:18,439
Her neck was bitten through.

65
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:19,800
Drained of blood.

66
00:04:21,639 --> 00:04:22,839
Could there really be a vengeful ghost?

67
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:30,439
Out of booze again.

68
00:04:43,319 --> 00:04:43,800
Have a seat.

69
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:51,560
Lao Jiugui.

70
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:52,920
Let's cut to the chase.

71
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:54,759
Three people died in one night.

72
00:04:54,759 --> 00:04:55,720
This is no small matter.

73
00:04:57,680 --> 00:04:59,079
Is it the work of a vengeful ghost?

74
00:04:59,079 --> 00:04:59,800
I don't know.

75
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:01,800
But looking at the necks,

76
00:05:02,879 --> 00:05:04,360
they seem to have been bitten by a beast.

77
00:05:04,399 --> 00:05:05,319
A beast?

78
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,160
A tiger or a bear?

79
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:08,480
Mayor.

80
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:09,040
Case solved.

81
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:11,519
It's either a tiger or a bear.

82
00:05:11,519 --> 00:05:12,079
That's what he said.

83
00:05:12,959 --> 00:05:13,240
Not me.

84
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:13,959
Shut up.

85
00:05:14,079 --> 00:05:15,000
No, no, it wasn't.

86
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:16,120
It was Old Man Zhang.

87
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:17,399
Which Old Man Zhang?

88
00:05:17,399 --> 00:05:19,279
The shoe-shiner at the city gate.

89
00:05:21,839 --> 00:05:22,399
Hold on.

90
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:23,759
You haven't paid me yet.

91
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:25,720
Pay for what?

92
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:26,639
Take a look.

93
00:05:26,959 --> 00:05:28,000
You got my socks all dirty.

94
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:29,560
You're lucky I'm not charging you.

95
00:05:29,759 --> 00:05:30,360
Pay for what?

96
00:05:35,319 --> 00:05:36,319
You saw it with your own eyes?

97
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:38,399
Yes, with my own eyes.

98
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:40,120
But his eyes were all white,

99
00:05:40,439 --> 00:05:41,519
his mouth full of long teeth,

100
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:42,480
he didn't look human.

101
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:44,079
Why are you telling me?

102
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:49,120
Brother-in-law, what do we do?

103
00:05:49,959 --> 00:05:50,759
You're useless.

104
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:52,480
Lao Jiugui.

105
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:53,800
So what

106
00:05:53,959 --> 00:05:54,720
do we do next?

107
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:56,639
You're the mayor.

108
00:05:56,959 --> 00:05:58,040
Don't ask me.

109
00:05:58,480 --> 00:05:59,240
Help me out here.

110
00:06:00,319 --> 00:06:02,000
Since he saw it himself,

111
00:06:02,399 --> 00:06:03,560
before he hurts anyone else,

112
00:06:03,759 --> 00:06:05,839
just bring him in for questioning.

113
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:06,680
Right, right.

114
00:06:07,199 --> 00:06:08,319
We're on the same page.

115
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:09,959
Arrest him!

116
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:13,040
Right, right, right.

117
00:06:40,399 --> 00:06:41,279
Old Man Zhang!

118
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:42,800
I know you're in there.

119
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:44,399
Come out now.

120
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:48,360
Go in and check.

121
00:06:49,279 --> 00:06:49,800
Lord Beile,

122
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:50,839
I'm too scared.

123
00:06:51,079 --> 00:06:52,079
Get in there or I'll shoot you.

124
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:00,399
Reporting in.

125
00:07:00,759 --> 00:07:01,480
No one's here.

126
00:07:02,199 --> 00:07:02,920
No one?

127
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:10,199
Old Man Zhang must've been scared

128
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:11,360
and fled out of guilt.

129
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:34,000
That scared me to death.

130
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:50,480
Help me.

131
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:05,120
Take him away.

132
00:08:05,959 --> 00:08:06,439
Yes, sir.

133
00:08:22,439 --> 00:08:23,040
Lao Jiugui.

134
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:24,360
Take a look, will you?

135
00:08:24,519 --> 00:08:25,199
Look at what?

136
00:08:26,439 --> 00:08:27,399
There's nothing I can do.

137
00:08:27,839 --> 00:08:28,480
The man's already dead.

138
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:29,240
What's there to look at?

139
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:30,399
He's dead?

140
00:08:30,399 --> 00:08:31,079
Mayor,

141
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:33,840
weren't we going to bring him in for questioning?

142
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:34,360
And now...

143
00:08:34,919 --> 00:08:35,360
Well...

144
00:08:35,919 --> 00:08:36,679
See for yourself.

145
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:39,960
Are you sure he's dead?

146
00:08:41,039 --> 00:08:43,039
If I, Lao Jiugui, say he's dead,

147
00:08:43,039 --> 00:08:44,600
then he's definitely dead.

148
00:08:46,159 --> 00:08:47,000
Good.

149
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:48,440
Good riddance!

150
00:08:49,679 --> 00:08:50,919
The killer has been brought to justice.

151
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:51,840
Case closed.

152
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:54,240
But what about the body?

153
00:08:55,639 --> 00:08:56,159
Toss it.

154
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:56,720
Burn it.

155
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:57,200
Bury it.

156
00:08:57,399 --> 00:08:57,720
Cook it.

157
00:08:57,720 --> 00:08:58,159
Fry it.

158
00:08:58,879 --> 00:08:59,639
Up to you.

159
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:01,879
It's all yours.

160
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:34,240
What's wrong?

161
00:09:37,519 --> 00:09:38,840
The body's gone.

162
00:10:04,879 --> 00:10:05,879
The eggs are still here.

163
00:10:06,559 --> 00:10:07,759
He didn't leave through here.

164
00:10:13,399 --> 00:10:13,799
This...

165
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:15,240
He went out through here.

166
00:10:16,759 --> 00:10:17,279
Ruling.

167
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:19,399
Go back and lock the doors and windows.

168
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:20,919
Until I come back,

169
00:10:20,919 --> 00:10:21,679
don't you dare come out.

170
00:10:22,279 --> 00:10:22,679
Let's go.

171
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:24,360
Where are you going?

172
00:10:25,759 --> 00:10:26,519
There's a door right there.

173
00:10:26,519 --> 00:10:27,679
Why are you climbing the wall?

174
00:11:25,279 --> 00:11:25,840
Lao Jiugui!

175
00:11:26,519 --> 00:11:27,399
What on earth is going on?

176
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:29,440
Isn't it obvious?

177
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:30,679
He got away.

178
00:11:30,799 --> 00:11:32,000
And he's hurt people again.

179
00:11:32,399 --> 00:11:33,399
Oh, give me a break.

180
00:11:33,639 --> 00:11:35,080
Who's going to believe that story?

181
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:36,080
Right now the townsfolk

182
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:37,679
are mobbing the town hall,

183
00:11:38,039 --> 00:11:38,960
demanding answers.

184
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:39,840
Mayor,

185
00:11:40,159 --> 00:11:42,480
just tell the people exactly what happened.

186
00:11:42,679 --> 00:11:44,240
The truth is always best.

187
00:11:44,759 --> 00:11:45,600
Cut the crap.

188
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:48,519
The corpse escaped from your Jigu Temple,

189
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:50,279
so you're responsible.

190
00:11:50,799 --> 00:11:51,480
Mayor,

191
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:54,000
the mayor's word is law, of course.

192
00:11:54,399 --> 00:11:54,919
People

193
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:55,879
can run.

194
00:11:56,159 --> 00:11:56,759
But corpses

195
00:11:56,879 --> 00:11:57,360
can't.

196
00:11:57,639 --> 00:11:58,639
If he ran off,

197
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:00,320
then he isn't a corpse.

198
00:12:00,320 --> 00:12:01,080
He's a person.

199
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:02,960
He's got nothing to do with our Jigu Temple.

200
00:12:03,639 --> 00:12:04,360
Nothing at all.

201
00:12:04,360 --> 00:12:05,240
Nothing, nothing whatsoever.

202
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:05,960
Lao Jiugui,

203
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:08,039
quit playing dumb.

204
00:12:08,039 --> 00:12:09,159
That corpse took two bullets.

205
00:12:09,159 --> 00:12:10,240
He was definitely dead.

206
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:11,399
How could he possibly escape?

207
00:12:12,039 --> 00:12:12,799
I suspect

208
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:14,200
you're the one behind this.

209
00:12:15,039 --> 00:12:15,919
Do tell.

210
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:18,440
I know you practice sorcery.

211
00:12:18,639 --> 00:12:20,000
You once summoned ghost soldiers, too.

212
00:12:20,279 --> 00:12:21,000
This time,

213
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:23,720
did you use your sorcery again

214
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:26,559
to control a corpse to harm the people,

215
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:28,440
and then rake in the money?

216
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:35,200
Isn't that what you pulled ten years ago?

217
00:12:36,440 --> 00:12:38,159
You think I won't shoot, do you?

218
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:39,320
Come on, come on.

219
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:40,080
Hurry up.

220
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:41,039
Let me lie down properly first.

221
00:12:41,039 --> 00:12:41,799
Come on, shoot.

222
00:12:41,799 --> 00:12:43,039
Who are you even talking to?
